snippet.textDisplay: Keep returning to hear this version often..... Very unfair comparisons are being made in comments on Humera v/s Nabeel. The critics choice is clearly Humera because she sang it with perfect balance only using a populist harkat at 2:50, on the other hand Nabeel used nasalization on higher notes which is easier for ordinary listeners (bathroom singers) to relate to when they try to copy the singer, but to be fair to Nabeel, this is a modern populist rendition and he did the acceptable thing.... I believe that he can sing the classical version just as easily to amaze the critics.... Excellent rendition by both singers.....
